rom writers as diverse as Lyn Hejinian, William Faulkner, and Joseph Roth. He takes up the status of the proper name in Modernism, with examples from Stein, Loy, and Guillaume Apollinaire, and he offers in-depth analyses of individual authors from the counter-canon of the avant-garde, including P. Inman, Russell Atkins, N. H. Pritchard, and Andy Warhol. The result is an inspiring intervention in contemporary poetics.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mai 2021) 0aLiterary style. 0aPoetics. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / General.2bisacsh  aAfrican American literature.  aavant-garde.  amateriality.  aonomastics.  apoetry and poetics.  aradical formalism.  areading.  asignifier.  atypography.1 aBooker, Peter, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCapote, Truman, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDerrida, Jacques, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDessoir, Max, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKant, Immanuel, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLowenfels, Walter, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMajor, René, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMorrison, Van, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aOndine,, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aStein, Gertrude, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishz978311070471608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020z9783110704518oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary, Cultural, Area Studies 2020 Englishz978311